<span class='talk-transcript__para__text'>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='759737' id='t-759737'>But here's the thing. Algorithms are rules. They're binary.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='763164' id='t-763164'>They're yes or no, they're black or white.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='764949' id='t-764949'>Truth is never binary. Truth is a value.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='768503' id='t-768503'>Truth is emotional, it's fluid, and above all, it's human.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='773167' id='t-773167'>No matter how quick we get with computers, no matter</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='775274' id='t-775274'>how much information we have, you'll never be able</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='777658' id='t-777658'>to remove the human from the truth-seeking exercise,</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='780654' id='t-780654'>because in the end, it is a uniquely human trait.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='784312' id='t-784312'>Thanks very much. (Applause)</span>
</span>
</p>
